2163/// Return true if the block containing the call site has a BlockFrequency of
2164/// less than ColdCCRelFreq% of the entry block.
2165static bool isColdCallSite(CallSite CS, BlockFrequencyInfo &CallerBFI) {
2166 const BranchProbability ColdProb(ColdCCRelFreq, 100);
2167 auto CallSiteBB = CS.getInstruction()->getParent();
2168 auto CallSiteFreq = CallerBFI.getBlockFreq(CallSiteBB);
2169 auto CallerEntryFreq =
2170 CallerBFI.getBlockFreq(&(CS.getCaller()->getEntryBlock()));
2171 return CallSiteFreq < CallerEntryFreq * ColdProb;
2172}
2173
2174// This function checks if the input function F is cold at all call sites. It
2175// also looks each call site's containing function, returning false if the
2176// caller function contains other non cold calls. The input vector AllCallsCold
2177// contains a list of functions that only have call sites in cold blocks.
2178static bool
2179isValidCandidateForColdCC(Function &F,
2180 function_ref<BlockFrequencyInfo &(Function &)> GetBFI,
2181 const std::vector<Function *> &AllCallsCold) {
2182
2183 if (F.user_empty())
2184 return false;
2185
2186 for (User *U : F.users()) {
2187 if (isa<BlockAddress>(U))
2188 continue;
2189
2190 CallSite CS(cast<Instruction>(U));
2191 Function *CallerFunc = CS.getInstruction()->getParent()->getParent();
2192 BlockFrequencyInfo &CallerBFI = GetBFI(*CallerFunc);
2193 if (!isColdCallSite(CS, CallerBFI))
2194 return false;
2195 auto It = std::find(AllCallsCold.begin(), AllCallsCold.end(), CallerFunc);
2196 if (It == AllCallsCold.end())
2197 return false;
2198 }
2199 return true;
2200}

2202static void changeCallSitesToColdCC(Function *F) {
2203 for (User *U : F->users()) {
2204 if (isa<BlockAddress>(U))
2205 continue;
2206 CallSite CS(cast<Instruction>(U));
2207 CS.setCallingConv(CallingConv::Cold);
2208 }
2209}
2210
2211// This function iterates over all the call instructions in the input Function
2212// and checks that all call sites are in cold blocks and are allowed to use the
2213// coldcc calling convention.
2214static bool
2215hasOnlyColdCalls(Function &F,
2216 function_ref<BlockFrequencyInfo &(Function &)> GetBFI) {
2217 for (BasicBlock &BB : F) {
2218 for (Instruction &I : BB) {
2219 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I)) {
2220 CallSite CS(cast<Instruction>(CI));
2221 // Skip over isline asm instructions since they aren't function calls.
2222 if (CI->isInlineAsm())
2223 continue;
2224 Function *CalledFn = CI->getCalledFunction();
2225 if (!CalledFn)
2226 return false;
2227 if (!CalledFn->hasLocalLinkage())
2228 return false;
2229 // Skip over instrinsics since they won't remain as function calls.
2230 if (CalledFn->getIntrinsicID() != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic)
2231 continue;
2232 // Check if it's valid to use coldcc calling convention.
2233 if (!hasChangeableCC(CalledFn) || CalledFn->isVarArg() ||
2234 CalledFn->hasAddressTaken())
2235 return false;
2236 BlockFrequencyInfo &CallerBFI = GetBFI(F);
2237 if (!isColdCallSite(CS, CallerBFI))
2238 return false;
2239 }
2240 }
2241 }
2242 return true;
2243}
2244
2245static bool
2246OptimizeFunctions(Module &M, TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2247 function_ref<TargetTransformInfo &(Function &)> GetTTI,
2248 function_ref<BlockFrequencyInfo &(Function &)> GetBFI,
2249 function_ref<DominatorTree &(Function &)> LookupDomTree,
2250 SmallPtrSetImpl<const Comdat *> &NotDiscardableComdats) {
2251
2252 bool Changed = false;
2253
2254 std::vector<Function *> AllCallsCold;
2255 for (Module::iterator FI = M.begin(), E = M.end(); FI != E;) {
2256 Function *F = &*FI++;
2257 if (hasOnlyColdCalls(*F, GetBFI))
2258 AllCallsCold.push_back(F);
2259 }
2260
2261 // Optimize functions.
2262 for (Module::iterator FI = M.begin(), E = M.end(); FI != E; ) {
2263 Function *F = &*FI++;
2264
2265 // Don't perform global opt pass on naked functions; we don't want fast
2266 // calling conventions for naked functions.
2267 if (F->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::Naked))
2268 continue;
2269
2270 // Functions without names cannot be referenced outside this module.
2271 if (!F->hasName() && !F->isDeclaration() && !F->hasLocalLinkage())
2272 F->setLinkage(GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
2273
2274 if (deleteIfDead(*F, NotDiscardableComdats)) {
2275 Changed = true;
2276 continue;
2277 }
2278
2279 // LLVM's definition of dominance allows instructions that are cyclic
2280 // in unreachable blocks, e.g.:
2281 // %pat = select i1 %condition, @global, i16* %pat
2282 // because any instruction dominates an instruction in a block that's
2283 // not reachable from entry.
2284 // So, remove unreachable blocks from the function, because a) there's
2285 // no point in analyzing them and b) GlobalOpt should otherwise grow
2286 // some more complicated logic to break these cycles.
2287 // Removing unreachable blocks might invalidate the dominator so we
2288 // recalculate it.
2289 if (!F->isDeclaration()) {
2290 if (removeUnreachableBlocks(*F)) {
2291 auto &DT = LookupDomTree(*F);
2292 DT.recalculate(*F);
2293 Changed = true;
2294 }
2295 }
2296
2297 Changed |= processGlobal(*F, TLI, LookupDomTree);
2298
2299 if (!F->hasLocalLinkage())
2300 continue;
2301
2302 // If we have an inalloca parameter that we can safely remove the
2303 // inalloca attribute from, do so. This unlocks optimizations that
2304 // wouldn't be safe in the presence of inalloca.
2305 // FIXME: We should also hoist alloca affected by this to the entry
2306 // block if possible.
2307 if (F->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::InAlloca) &&
2308 !F->hasAddressTaken()) {
2309 RemoveAttribute(F, Attribute::InAlloca);
2310 Changed = true;
2311 }
2312
2313 if (hasChangeableCC(F) && !F->isVarArg() && !F->hasAddressTaken()) {
2314 NumInternalFunc++;
2315 TargetTransformInfo &TTI = GetTTI(*F);
2316 // Change the calling convention to coldcc if either stress testing is
2317 // enabled or the target would like to use coldcc on functions which are
2318 // cold at all call sites and the callers contain no other non coldcc
2319 // calls.
2320 if (EnableColdCCStressTest ||
2321 (TTI.useColdCCForColdCall(*F) &&
2322 isValidCandidateForColdCC(*F, GetBFI, AllCallsCold))) {
2323 F->setCallingConv(CallingConv::Cold);
2324 changeCallSitesToColdCC(F);
2325 Changed = true;
2326 NumColdCC++;
2327 }
2328 }
2329
2330 if (hasChangeableCC(F) && !F->isVarArg() &&
2331 !F->hasAddressTaken()) {
2332 // If this function has a calling convention worth changing, is not a
2333 // varargs function, and is only called directly, promote it to use the
2334 // Fast calling convention.
2335 F->setCallingConv(CallingConv::Fast);
2336 ChangeCalleesToFastCall(F);
2337 ++NumFastCallFns;
2338 Changed = true;
2339 }
2340
2341 if (F->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::Nest) &&
2342 !F->hasAddressTaken()) {
2343 // The function is not used by a trampoline intrinsic, so it is safe
2344 // to remove the 'nest' attribute.
2345 RemoveAttribute(F, Attribute::Nest);
2346 ++NumNestRemoved;
2347 Changed = true;
2348 }
2349 }
2350 return Changed;
2351}
2352
2353static bool
2354OptimizeGlobalVars(Module &M, TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2355 function_ref<DominatorTree &(Function &)> LookupDomTree,
2356 SmallPtrSetImpl<const Comdat *> &NotDiscardableComdats) {
2357 bool Changed = false;
2358
2359 for (Module::global_iterator GVI = M.global_begin(), E = M.global_end();
2360 GVI != E; ) {
2361 GlobalVariable *GV = &*GVI++;
2362 // Global variables without names cannot be referenced outside this module.
2363 if (!GV->hasName() && !GV->isDeclaration() && !GV->hasLocalLinkage())
2364 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
2365 // Simplify the initializer.
2366 if (GV->hasInitializer())
2367 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(GV->getInitializer())) {
2368 auto &DL = M.getDataLayout();
2369 Constant *New = ConstantFoldConstant(C, DL, TLI);
2370 if (New && New != C)
2371 GV->setInitializer(New);
2372 }
2373
2374 if (deleteIfDead(*GV, NotDiscardableComdats)) {
2375 Changed = true;
2376 continue;
2377 }
2378
2379 Changed |= processGlobal(*GV, TLI, LookupDomTree);
2380 }
2381 return Changed;
2382}
2383
2384/// Evaluate a piece of a constantexpr store into a global initializer. This
2385/// returns 'Init' modified to reflect 'Val' stored into it. At this point, the
2386/// GEP operands of Addr [0, OpNo) have been stepped into.
2387static Constant *EvaluateStoreInto(Constant *Init, Constant *Val,
2388 ConstantExpr *Addr, unsigned OpNo) {
2389 // Base case of the recursion.
2390 if (OpNo == Addr->getNumOperands()) {
2391 assert(Val->getType() == Init->getType() && "Type mismatch!");
2392 return Val;
2393 }
2394
2395 SmallVector<Constant*, 32> Elts;
2396 if (StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(Init->getType())) {
2397 // Break up the constant into its elements.
2398 for (unsigned i = 0, e = STy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i)
2399 Elts.push_back(Init->getAggregateElement(i));
2400
2401 // Replace the element that we are supposed to.
2402 ConstantInt *CU = cast<ConstantInt>(Addr->getOperand(OpNo));
2403 unsigned Idx = CU->getZExtValue();
2404 assert(Idx < STy->getNumElements() && "Struct index out of range!");
2405 Elts[Idx] = EvaluateStoreInto(Elts[Idx], Val, Addr, OpNo+1);
2406
2407 // Return the modified struct.
2408 return ConstantStruct::get(STy, Elts);
2409 }
2410
2411 ConstantInt *CI = cast<ConstantInt>(Addr->getOperand(OpNo));
2412 SequentialType *InitTy = cast<SequentialType>(Init->getType());
2413 uint64_t NumElts = InitTy->getNumElements();
2414
2415 // Break up the array into elements.
2416 for (uint64_t i = 0, e = NumElts; i != e; ++i)
2417 Elts.push_back(Init->getAggregateElement(i));
2418
2419 assert(CI->getZExtValue() < NumElts);
2420 Elts[CI->getZExtValue()] =
2421 EvaluateStoreInto(Elts[CI->getZExtValue()], Val, Addr, OpNo+1);
2422
2423 if (Init->getType()->isArrayTy())
2424 return ConstantArray::get(cast<ArrayType>(InitTy), Elts);
2425 return ConstantVector::get(Elts);
2426}
2427
2428/// We have decided that Addr (which satisfies the predicate
2429/// isSimpleEnoughPointerToCommit) should get Val as its value. Make it happen.
2430static void CommitValueTo(Constant *Val, Constant *Addr) {
2431 if (GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(Addr)) {
2432 assert(GV->hasInitializer());
2433 GV->setInitializer(Val);
2434 return;
2435 }
2436
2437 ConstantExpr *CE = cast<ConstantExpr>(Addr);
2438 GlobalVariable *GV = cast<GlobalVariable>(CE->getOperand(0));
2439 GV->setInitializer(EvaluateStoreInto(GV->getInitializer(), Val, CE, 2));
2440}
2441
2442/// Given a map of address -> value, where addresses are expected to be some form
2443/// of either a global or a constant GEP, set the initializer for the address to
2444/// be the value. This performs mostly the same function as CommitValueTo()
2445/// and EvaluateStoreInto() but is optimized to be more efficient for the common
2446/// case where the set of addresses are GEPs sharing the same underlying global,
2447/// processing the GEPs in batches rather than individually.
2448///
2449/// To give an example, consider the following C++ code adapted from the clang
2450/// regression tests:
2451/// struct S {
2452/// int n = 10;
2453/// int m = 2 * n;
2454/// S(int a) : n(a) {}
2455/// };
2456///
2457/// template<typename T>
2458/// struct U {
2459/// T *r = &q;
2460/// T q = 42;
2461/// U *p = this;
2462/// };
2463///
2464/// U<S> e;
2465///
2466/// The global static constructor for 'e' will need to initialize 'r' and 'p' of
2467/// the outer struct, while also initializing the inner 'q' structs 'n' and 'm'
2468/// members. This batch algorithm will simply use general CommitValueTo() method
2469/// to handle the complex nested S struct initialization of 'q', before
2470/// processing the outermost members in a single batch. Using CommitValueTo() to
2471/// handle member in the outer struct is inefficient when the struct/array is
2472/// very large as we end up creating and destroy constant arrays for each
2473/// initialization.
2474/// For the above case, we expect the following IR to be generated:
2475///
2476/// %struct.U = type { %struct.S*, %struct.S, %struct.U* }
2477/// %struct.S = type { i32, i32 }
2478/// @e = global %struct.U { %struct.S* gep inbounds (%struct.U, %struct.U* @e,
2479/// i64 0, i32 1),
2480/// %struct.S { i32 42, i32 84 }, %struct.U* @e }
2481/// The %struct.S { i32 42, i32 84 } inner initializer is treated as a complex
2482/// constant expression, while the other two elements of @e are "simple".
2483static void BatchCommitValueTo(const DenseMap<Constant*, Constant*> &Mem) {
2484 SmallVector<std::pair<GlobalVariable*, Constant*>, 32> GVs;
2485 SmallVector<std::pair<ConstantExpr*, Constant*>, 32> ComplexCEs;
2486 SmallVector<std::pair<ConstantExpr*, Constant*>, 32> SimpleCEs;
2487 SimpleCEs.reserve(Mem.size());
2488
2489 for (const auto &I : Mem) {
2490 if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(I.first)) {
2491 GVs.push_back(std::make_pair(GV, I.second));
2492 } else {
2493 ConstantExpr *GEP = cast<ConstantExpr>(I.first);
2494 // We don't handle the deeply recursive case using the batch method.
2495 if (GEP->getNumOperands() > 3)
2496 ComplexCEs.push_back(std::make_pair(GEP, I.second));
2497 else
2498 SimpleCEs.push_back(std::make_pair(GEP, I.second));
2499 }
2500 }
2501
2502 // The algorithm below doesn't handle cases like nested structs, so use the
2503 // slower fully general method if we have to.
2504 for (auto ComplexCE : ComplexCEs)
2505 CommitValueTo(ComplexCE.second, ComplexCE.first);
2506
2507 for (auto GVPair : GVs) {
2508 assert(GVPair.first->hasInitializer());
2509 GVPair.first->setInitializer(GVPair.second);
2510 }
2511
2512 if (SimpleCEs.empty())
2513 return;
2514
2515 // We cache a single global's initializer elements in the case where the
2516 // subsequent address/val pair uses the same one. This avoids throwing away and
2517 // rebuilding the constant struct/vector/array just because one element is
2518 // modified at a time.
2519 SmallVector<Constant *, 32> Elts;
2520 Elts.reserve(SimpleCEs.size());
2521 GlobalVariable *CurrentGV = nullptr;
2522
2523 auto commitAndSetupCache = [&](GlobalVariable *GV, bool Update) {
2524 Constant *Init = GV->getInitializer();
2525 Type *Ty = Init->getType();
2526 if (Update) {
2527 if (CurrentGV) {
2528 assert(CurrentGV && "Expected a GV to commit to!");
2529 Type *CurrentInitTy = CurrentGV->getInitializer()->getType();
2530 // We have a valid cache that needs to be committed.
2531 if (StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(CurrentInitTy))
2532 CurrentGV->setInitializer(ConstantStruct::get(STy, Elts));
2533 else if (ArrayType *ArrTy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(CurrentInitTy))
2534 CurrentGV->setInitializer(ConstantArray::get(ArrTy, Elts));
2535 else
2536 CurrentGV->setInitializer(ConstantVector::get(Elts));
2537 }
2538 if (CurrentGV == GV)
2539 return;
2540 // Need to clear and set up cache for new initializer.
2541 CurrentGV = GV;
2542 Elts.clear();
2543 unsigned NumElts;
2544 if (auto *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(Ty))
2545 NumElts = STy->getNumElements();
2546 else
2547 NumElts = cast<SequentialType>(Ty)->getNumElements();
2548 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumElts; i != e; ++i)
2549 Elts.push_back(Init->getAggregateElement(i));
2550 }
2551 };
2552
2553 for (auto CEPair : SimpleCEs) {
2554 ConstantExpr *GEP = CEPair.first;
2555 Constant *Val = CEPair.second;
2556
2557 GlobalVariable *GV = cast<GlobalVariable>(GEP->getOperand(0));
2558 commitAndSetupCache(GV, GV != CurrentGV);
2559 ConstantInt *CI = cast<ConstantInt>(GEP->getOperand(2));
2560 Elts[CI->getZExtValue()] = Val;
2561 }
2562 // The last initializer in the list needs to be committed, others
2563 // will be committed on a new initializer being processed.
2564 commitAndSetupCache(CurrentGV, true);
2565}
2566
2567/// Evaluate static constructors in the function, if we can. Return true if we
2568/// can, false otherwise.
2569static bool EvaluateStaticConstructor(Function *F, const DataLayout &DL,
2570 TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
2571 // Call the function.
2572 Evaluator Eval(DL, TLI);
2573 Constant *RetValDummy;
2574 bool EvalSuccess = Eval.EvaluateFunction(F, RetValDummy,
2575 SmallVector<Constant*, 0>());
2576
2577 if (EvalSuccess) {
2578 ++NumCtorsEvaluated;
2579
2580 // We succeeded at evaluation: commit the result.
2581 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FULLY EVALUATED GLOBAL CTOR FUNCTION '"
2582 << F->getName() << "' to "
2583 << Eval.getMutatedMemory().size() << " stores.\n");
2584 BatchCommitValueTo(Eval.getMutatedMemory());
2585 for (GlobalVariable *GV : Eval.getInvariants())
2586 GV->setConstant(true);
2587 }
2588
2589 return EvalSuccess;
2590}

2592static int compareNames(Constant *const *A, Constant *const *B) {
2593 Value *AStripped = (*A)->stripPointerCastsNoFollowAliases();
2594 Value *BStripped = (*B)->stripPointerCastsNoFollowAliases();
2595 return AStripped->getName().compare(BStripped->getName());
2596}
2597
2598static void setUsedInitializer(GlobalVariable &V,
2599 const SmallPtrSetImpl<GlobalValue *> &Init) {
2600 if (Init.empty()) {
2601 V.eraseFromParent();
2602 return;
2603 }
2604
2605 // Type of pointer to the array of pointers.
2606 PointerType *Int8PtrTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(V.getContext(), 0);
2607
2608 SmallVector<Constant *, 8> UsedArray;
2609 for (GlobalValue *GV : Init) {
2610 Constant *Cast
2611 = ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(GV, Int8PtrTy);
2612 UsedArray.push_back(Cast);
2613 }
2614 // Sort to get deterministic order.
2615 array_pod_sort(UsedArray.begin(), UsedArray.end(), compareNames);
2616 ArrayType *ATy = ArrayType::get(Int8PtrTy, UsedArray.size());
2617
2618 Module *M = V.getParent();
2619 V.removeFromParent();
2620 GlobalVariable *NV =
2621 new GlobalVariable(*M, ATy, false, GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage,
2622 ConstantArray::get(ATy, UsedArray), "");
2623 NV->takeName(&V);
2624 NV->setSection("llvm.metadata");
2625 delete &V;
2626}

2630/// An easy to access representation of llvm.used and llvm.compiler.used.
2631class LLVMUsed {
2632 SmallPtrSet<GlobalValue *, 8> Used;
2633 SmallPtrSet<GlobalValue *, 8> CompilerUsed;
2634 GlobalVariable *UsedV;
2635 GlobalVariable *CompilerUsedV;
2636
2637public:
2638 LLVMUsed(Module &M) {
2639 UsedV = collectUsedGlobalVariables(M, Used, false);
2640 CompilerUsedV = collectUsedGlobalVariables(M, CompilerUsed, true);
2641 }
2642
2643 using iterator = SmallPtrSet<GlobalValue *, 8>::iterator;
2644 using used_iterator_range = iterator_range<iterator>;
2645
2646 iterator usedBegin() { return Used.begin(); }
2647 iterator usedEnd() { return Used.end(); }
2648
2649 used_iterator_range used() {
2650 return used_iterator_range(usedBegin(), usedEnd());
2651 }
2652
2653 iterator compilerUsedBegin() { return CompilerUsed.begin(); }
2654 iterator compilerUsedEnd() { return CompilerUsed.end(); }
2655
2656 used_iterator_range compilerUsed() {
2657 return used_iterator_range(compilerUsedBegin(), compilerUsedEnd());
2658 }
2659
2660 bool usedCount(GlobalValue *GV) const { return Used.count(GV); }
2661
2662 bool compilerUsedCount(GlobalValue *GV) const {
2663 return CompilerUsed.count(GV);
2664 }
2665
2666 bool usedErase(GlobalValue *GV) { return Used.erase(GV); }
2667 bool compilerUsedErase(GlobalValue *GV) { return CompilerUsed.erase(GV); }
2668 bool usedInsert(GlobalValue *GV) { return Used.insert(GV).second; }
2669
2670 bool compilerUsedInsert(GlobalValue *GV) {
2671 return CompilerUsed.insert(GV).second;
2672 }
2673
2674 void syncVariablesAndSets() {
2675 if (UsedV)
2676 setUsedInitializer(*UsedV, Used);
2677 if (CompilerUsedV)
2678 setUsedInitializer(*CompilerUsedV, CompilerUsed);
2679 }
2680};

2683
2684static bool hasUseOtherThanLLVMUsed(GlobalAlias &GA, const LLVMUsed &U) {
2685 if (GA.use_empty()) // No use at all.
2686 return false;
2687
2688 assert((!U.usedCount(&GA) || !U.compilerUsedCount(&GA)) &&
2689 "We should have removed the duplicated "
2690 "element from llvm.compiler.used");
2691 if (!GA.hasOneUse())
2692 // Strictly more than one use. So at least one is not in llvm.used and
2693 // llvm.compiler.used.
2694 return true;
2695
2696 // Exactly one use. Check if it is in llvm.used or llvm.compiler.used.
2697 return !U.usedCount(&GA) && !U.compilerUsedCount(&GA);
2698}
2699
2700static bool hasMoreThanOneUseOtherThanLLVMUsed(GlobalValue &V,
2701 const LLVMUsed &U) {
2702 unsigned N = 2;
2703 assert((!U.usedCount(&V) || !U.compilerUsedCount(&V)) &&
2704 "We should have removed the duplicated "
2705 "element from llvm.compiler.used");
2706 if (U.usedCount(&V) || U.compilerUsedCount(&V))
2707 ++N;
2708 return V.hasNUsesOrMore(N);
2709}
2710
2711static bool mayHaveOtherReferences(GlobalAlias &GA, const LLVMUsed &U) {
2712 if (!GA.hasLocalLinkage())
2713 return true;
2714
2715 return U.usedCount(&GA) || U.compilerUsedCount(&GA);
2716}
2717
2718static bool hasUsesToReplace(GlobalAlias &GA, const LLVMUsed &U,
2719 bool &RenameTarget) {
2720 RenameTarget = false;
2721 bool Ret = false;
2722 if (hasUseOtherThanLLVMUsed(GA, U))
2723 Ret = true;
2724
2725 // If the alias is externally visible, we may still be able to simplify it.
2726 if (!mayHaveOtherReferences(GA, U))
2727 return Ret;
2728
2729 // If the aliasee has internal linkage, give it the name and linkage
2730 // of the alias, and delete the alias. This turns:
2731 // define internal ... @f(...)
2732 // @a = alias ... @f
2733 // into:
2734 // define ... @a(...)
2735 Constant *Aliasee = GA.getAliasee();
2736 GlobalValue *Target = cast<GlobalValue>(Aliasee->stripPointerCasts());
2737 if (!Target->hasLocalLinkage())
2738 return Ret;
2739
2740 // Do not perform the transform if multiple aliases potentially target the
2741 // aliasee. This check also ensures that it is safe to replace the section
2742 // and other attributes of the aliasee with those of the alias.
2743 if (hasMoreThanOneUseOtherThanLLVMUsed(*Target, U))
2744 return Ret;
2745
2746 RenameTarget = true;
2747 return true;
2748}
2749
2750static bool
2751OptimizeGlobalAliases(Module &M,
2752 SmallPtrSetImpl<const Comdat *> &NotDiscardableComdats) {
2753 bool Changed = false;
2754 LLVMUsed Used(M);
2755
2756 for (GlobalValue *GV : Used.used())
2757 Used.compilerUsedErase(GV);
2758
2759 for (Module::alias_iterator I = M.alias_begin(), E = M.alias_end();
2760 I != E;) {
2761 GlobalAlias *J = &*I++;
2762
2763 // Aliases without names cannot be referenced outside this module.
2764 if (!J->hasName() && !J->isDeclaration() && !J->hasLocalLinkage())
2765 J->setLinkage(GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
2766
2767 if (deleteIfDead(*J, NotDiscardableComdats)) {
2768 Changed = true;
2769 continue;
2770 }
2771
2772 // If the alias can change at link time, nothing can be done - bail out.
2773 if (J->isInterposable())
2774 continue;
2775
2776 Constant *Aliasee = J->getAliasee();
2777 GlobalValue *Target = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(Aliasee->stripPointerCasts());
2778 // We can't trivially replace the alias with the aliasee if the aliasee is
2779 // non-trivial in some way.
2780 // TODO: Try to handle non-zero GEPs of local aliasees.
2781 if (!Target)
2782 continue;
2783 Target->removeDeadConstantUsers();
2784
2785 // Make all users of the alias use the aliasee instead.
2786 bool RenameTarget;
2787 if (!hasUsesToReplace(*J, Used, RenameTarget))
2788 continue;
2789
2790 J->replaceAllUsesWith(ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Aliasee, J->getType()));
2791 ++NumAliasesResolved;
2792 Changed = true;
2793
2794 if (RenameTarget) {
2795 // Give the aliasee the name, linkage and other attributes of the alias.
2796 Target->takeName(&*J);
2797 Target->setLinkage(J->getLinkage());
2798 Target->setDSOLocal(J->isDSOLocal());
2799 Target->setVisibility(J->getVisibility());
2800 Target->setDLLStorageClass(J->getDLLStorageClass());
2801
2802 if (Used.usedErase(&*J))
2803 Used.usedInsert(Target);
2804
2805 if (Used.compilerUsedErase(&*J))
2806 Used.compilerUsedInsert(Target);
2807 } else if (mayHaveOtherReferences(*J, Used))
2808 continue;
2809
2810 // Delete the alias.
2811 M.getAliasList().erase(J);
2812 ++NumAliasesRemoved;
2813 Changed = true;
2814 }
2815
2816 Used.syncVariablesAndSets();
2817
2818 return Changed;
2819}

2821static Function *FindCXAAtExit(Module &M, TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
2822 LibFunc F = LibFunc_cxa_atexit;
2823 if (!TLI->has(F))
2824 return nullptr;
2825
2826 Function *Fn = M.getFunction(TLI->getName(F));
2827 if (!Fn)
2828 return nullptr;
2829
2830 // Make sure that the function has the correct prototype.
2831 if (!TLI->getLibFunc(*Fn, F) || F != LibFunc_cxa_atexit)
2832 return nullptr;
2833
2834 return Fn;
2835}
2836
2837/// Returns whether the given function is an empty C++ destructor and can
2838/// therefore be eliminated.
2839/// Note that we assume that other optimization passes have already simplified
2840/// the code so we simply check for 'ret'.
2841static bool cxxDtorIsEmpty(const Function &Fn) {
2842 // FIXME: We could eliminate C++ destructors if they're readonly/readnone and
2843 // nounwind, but that doesn't seem worth doing.
2844 if (Fn.isDeclaration())
2845 return false;
2846
2847 for (auto &I : Fn.getEntryBlock()) {
2848 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
2849 continue;
2850 if (isa<ReturnInst>(I))
2851 return true;
2852 break;
2853 }
2854 return false;
2855}
2856
2857static bool OptimizeEmptyGlobalCXXDtors(Function *CXAAtExitFn) {
2858 /// Itanium C++ ABI p3.3.5:
2859 ///
2860 /// After constructing a global (or local static) object, that will require
2861 /// destruction on exit, a termination function is registered as follows:
2862 ///
2863 /// extern "C" int __cxa_atexit ( void (*f)(void *), void *p, void *d );
2864 ///
2865 /// This registration, e.g. __cxa_atexit(f,p,d), is intended to cause the
2866 /// call f(p) when DSO d is unloaded, before all such termination calls
2867 /// registered before this one. It returns zero if registration is
2868 /// successful, nonzero on failure.
2869
2870 // This pass will look for calls to __cxa_atexit where the function is trivial
2871 // and remove them.
2872 bool Changed = false;
2873
2874 for (auto I = CXAAtExitFn->user_begin(), E = CXAAtExitFn->user_end();
2875 I != E;) {
2876 // We're only interested in calls. Theoretically, we could handle invoke
2877 // instructions as well, but neither llvm-gcc nor clang generate invokes
2878 // to __cxa_atexit.
2879 CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(*I++);
2880 if (!CI)
2881 continue;
2882
2883 Function *DtorFn =
2884 dyn_cast<Function>(CI->getArgOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts());
2885 if (!DtorFn || !cxxDtorIsEmpty(*DtorFn))
2886 continue;
2887
2888 // Just remove the call.
2889 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()));
2890 CI->eraseFromParent();
2891
2892 ++NumCXXDtorsRemoved;
2893
2894 Changed |= true;
2895 }
2896
2897 return Changed;
2898}
2899
2900static bool optimizeGlobalsInModule(
2901 Module &M, const DataLayout &DL, TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2902 function_ref<TargetTransformInfo &(Function &)> GetTTI,
2903 function_ref<BlockFrequencyInfo &(Function &)> GetBFI,
2904 function_ref<DominatorTree &(Function &)> LookupDomTree) {
2905 SmallPtrSet<const Comdat *, 8> NotDiscardableComdats;
2906 bool Changed = false;
2907 bool LocalChange = true;
2908 while (LocalChange) {
2909 LocalChange = false;
2910
2911 NotDiscardableComdats.clear();
2912 for (const GlobalVariable &GV : M.globals())
2913 if (const Comdat *C = GV.getComdat())
2914 if (!GV.isDiscardableIfUnused() || !GV.use_empty())
2915 NotDiscardableComdats.insert(C);
2916 for (Function &F : M)
2917 if (const Comdat *C = F.getComdat())
2918 if (!F.isDefTriviallyDead())
2919 NotDiscardableComdats.insert(C);
2920 for (GlobalAlias &GA : M.aliases())
2921 if (const Comdat *C = GA.getComdat())
2922 if (!GA.isDiscardableIfUnused() || !GA.use_empty())
2923 NotDiscardableComdats.insert(C);
2924
2925 // Delete functions that are trivially dead, ccc -> fastcc
2926 LocalChange |= OptimizeFunctions(M, TLI, GetTTI, GetBFI, LookupDomTree,
2927 NotDiscardableComdats);
2928
2929 // Optimize global_ctors list.
2930 LocalChange |= optimizeGlobalCtorsList(M, [&](Function *F) {
2931 return EvaluateStaticConstructor(F, DL, TLI);
2932 });
2933
2934 // Optimize non-address-taken globals.
2935 LocalChange |= OptimizeGlobalVars(M, TLI, LookupDomTree,
2936 NotDiscardableComdats);
2937
2938 // Resolve aliases, when possible.
2939 LocalChange |= OptimizeGlobalAliases(M, NotDiscardableComdats);
2940
2941 // Try to remove trivial global destructors if they are not removed
2942 // already.
2943 Function *CXAAtExitFn = FindCXAAtExit(M, TLI);
2944 if (CXAAtExitFn)
2945 LocalChange |= OptimizeEmptyGlobalCXXDtors(CXAAtExitFn);
2946
2947 Changed |= LocalChange;
2948 }
2949
2950 // TODO: Move all global ctors functions to the end of the module for code
2951 // layout.
2952
2953 return Changed;
2954}
2955
2956PreservedAnalyses GlobalOptPass::run(Module &M, ModuleAnalysisManager &AM) {
2957 auto &DL = M.getDataLayout();
2958 auto &TLI = AM.getResult<TargetLibraryAnalysis>(M);
2959 auto &FAM =
2960 AM.getResult<FunctionAnalysisManagerModuleProxy>(M).getManager();
2961 auto LookupDomTree = [&FAM](Function &F) -> DominatorTree &{
2962 return FAM.getResult<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(F);
2963 };
2964 auto GetTTI = [&FAM](Function &F) -> TargetTransformInfo & {
2965 return FAM.getResult<TargetIRAnalysis>(F);
2966 };
2967
2968 auto GetBFI = [&FAM](Function &F) -> BlockFrequencyInfo & {
2969 return FAM.getResult<BlockFrequencyAnalysis>(F);
2970 };
2971
2972 if (!optimizeGlobalsInModule(M, DL, &TLI, GetTTI, GetBFI, LookupDomTree))
2973 return PreservedAnalyses::all();
2974 return PreservedAnalyses::none();
2975}
